Paramedics say the boy was playing in a yard when he touched the live wire. JOHANNESBURG - A two-year-old boy has been electrocuted by an exposed electricity cable at an informal settlement. Paramedics say the boy was playing in a yard on Wednesday afternoon when he touched the live wire. ER24's Russel Meiring says the boy was certified dead on the scene. The ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene and found prevention services performing CPR on the child. We immediately assisted but unfortunately after 30 minutes of CPR no life signs were returned and he was pronounced dead on the scene. It s the second child to be electrocuted in Gauteng this week. On Monday, a six-year-old girl died in the Thembelihle Informal Settlement after coming into contact with a live wire.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)